<center><font face="Arial"><font color="#3333FF"><font size=+1>Staff contd.</font></font></font></center>

<blockquote><b><i><font face="Arial">TeamCenter:</font></i></b></blockquote>

<ol>
<ol>
<li>
No alerts. But TeamCenter provides a comprehensive email-based notification
system.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
After getting email from Project Manager the Staff can get the information
about their task through Quick Views. <br>
<BR></li>

<li>
The Notebooks are real-time shared workspaces where members can share and
organize information, ideas, documents, web links, and notes. Team members
can even work within the same notebook at the same time Team Center ensures
that each change identified by author and keeps all information synchronized
and up to date.</li>

<li>
Group discussion threads are allowed.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
TeamCenter Web-base timesheet system is an easy way to collect time and
report progress for organizations that must provide an accurate time accounting
audit trail for hours worked on projects.<br>
<BR></li>
</ol>
<b><i><font face="Arial">Microsoft Project Central:</font></i></b>
<br><b><i><font face="Arial"></font></i></b>&nbsp;
<ol>
<li>
No alerts. Communication through emails.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
TimeSheets: this where team members can see their assignments across projects,
enter updates and easily send them to the project manager.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
Team members can see their own tasks presented graphically in the Microsoft
Project Central Gantt Chart view.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
Team members can track and report actual hours spent on each assigned task.<br>
<BR></li>

<li>
Team members can create tasks. The project manager has to approve those
new tasks before adding to the project plan.</li>
</ol>
</ol>

</body>
